cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE

The paper focuses on adversarial attacks on neural network-based anomaly detection systems in industrial control systems (ICSs), which are cyber-physical systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes algorithms for generating poison samples and evaluates them on synthetic and real-world ICS data, which suggests that it belongs to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
